===Etymology===
From [[Mag]], a nickname for [[Margaret]] that was used to denote a [[chatterer]], and [[pie#Etymology_2|pie]], an archaic word meaning "magpie", from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|pie|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|pica|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*(s)peik-||woodpecker, magpie}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈmæɡˌpaɪ/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/"m{g%paI/}}
* {{hyphenation|mag|pie}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# One of several kinds of [[bird]] in the family [[Corvidae]], especially {{taxlink|Pica pica|species}}.
# A superficially similar Australian bird, {{taxlink|Gymnorhina tibicen|species}}.
# Someone who displays a magpie-like quality such as collecting, or committing robbery.
# {{context|slang|lang=en}} Fan or member of {{w|Newcastle United F.C.}}

